{"id":1190,"date":"2016-08-15T08:34:54","date_gmt":"2016-08-15T12:34:54","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/?p=1190"},"modified":"2017-05-23T12:36:46","modified_gmt":"2017-05-23T16:36:46","slug":"icp-researcher-develops-new-tools-for-survey-data","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/icp-researcher-develops-new-tools-for-survey-data\/","title":{"rendered":"ICP Researcher Develops New Tools for Survey Data"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"fcbkbttn_buttons_block\" id=\"fcbkbttn_left\"><\/div><div id=\"attachment_1193\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\"><a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/IMG2154_EM_ICPA.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1193\" class=\"wp-image-1193 size-medium\" src=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/IMG2154_EM_ICPA-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"Dr. Kelly Garbach (center) speaks with Mark Longstroth (Michigan State University Extension) about results from the 2015 ICP survey of growers' pollination practices.\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/IMG2154_EM_ICPA-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/IMG2154_EM_ICPA-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/IMG2154_EM_ICPA-1024x683.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-1193\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Dr. Kelly Garbach (center) speaks with Mark Longstroth (MSU Extension) about results from the 2015 ICP survey of growers&#8217; pollination practices.\u00a0<em>Photo: Emily May.<\/em><\/p><\/div>\n<p>Project ICP researcher Kelly Garbach (<a href=\"http:\/\/www.pointblue.org\/about-pointblue\/our-team\/ke\">Point Blue Conservation Science<\/a>, formerly Loyola University-Chicago), in collaboration with Geoffrey Morgan (<a href=\"http:\/\/www.gp-morgan.org\/\">Carnegie Mellon University<\/a>), has developed two publicly-available, open-source programs\u00a0for anonymizing and cleaning up data from large surveys.<\/p>\n<p>As part of the Integrated Crop Pollination project, Dr. Garbach conducted a multi-state survey of specialty crop growers in collaboration with the USDA National Agricultural Statistics Service.<\/p>\n<p>&#8220;Analyzing the survey data was an exciting challenge,&#8221; says Garbach. &#8220;We had to keep the data totally anonymous, while keeping enough detail to analyze key network connections.&#8221; These connections include information sharing in the agricultural community, including sharing information about pollinator management among growers, extension specialists, beekeepers and others.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1195\" style=\"width: 160px\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\"><a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/Morgan-and-Garbach-2016_White-Paper-ICP-2016.1R.pdf\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1195\" class=\"wp-image-1195 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/White-paper-150x150.png\" alt=\"White paper\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" srcset=\"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/White-paper-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/White-paper-230x230.png 230w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-1195\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Click thumbnail to read the new white paper!<\/p><\/div>\n<p>Garbach and Morgan developed two open-source tools to tackle this challenge, called\u00a0&#8220;Anonymizer&#8221; and &#8220;Linker.&#8221; Both are\u00a0described in more depth in <a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/Morgan-and-Garbach-2016_White-Paper-ICP-2016.1R.pdf\">this new white paper<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>See the quick start guides Garbach and Morgan developed for <a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/Anonymizer-QuickStart-Guide.pdf\">Anonymizer<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/Linker-QuickStart-Guide.pdf\">Linker<\/a>\u00a0for\u00a0an overview of what these computational tools can do and step-by-step instructions\u00a0for using\u00a0them. Click <a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/KellyGarbach\/SurveyInference\/tree\/1372d4abb6431d48996ffb6ed57e9d0242a2e750\/Executables\">here<\/a> to access the free downloadable program files\u00a0from\u00a0GitHub.<\/p>\n<p>Read more about\u00a0results from the Project ICP\/USDA-NASS pollination survey in different US crops and regions in these blog posts:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/survey-of-michigan-blueberry-growers\/\">Michigan blueberry<\/a>\u00a0survey<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/survey-report-on-california-almond-growers-pollination-practices-released\/\">California almond<\/a>\u00a0survey<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/survey-report-on-florida-blueberry-growers-pollination-practices-released\/\">Florida blueberry<\/a>\u00a0survey<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Project ICP researcher Kelly Garbach (Point Blue Conservation Science, formerly Loyola University-Chicago), in collaboration with Geoffrey Morgan (Carnegie Mellon University), has developed two publicly-available, open-source programs\u00a0for anonymizing and cleaning up data from large surveys. As part of the Integrated Crop&hellip; <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":5,"featured_media":1193,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_exactmetrics_skip_tracking":false,"_exactmetrics_sitenote_active":false,"_exactmetrics_sitenote_note":"","_exactmetrics_sitenote_category":0,"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":true,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":true,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_image_id":0,"font":"","enabled":false},"version":2}},"categories":[9],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-1190","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-project-icp-news-and-press"],"jetpack_publicize_connections":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/08\/IMG2154_EM_ICPA.jpg","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p58KSL-jc","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1190","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/5"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1190"}],"version-history":[{"count":7,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1190\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":1226,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1190\/revisions\/1226"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/1193"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1190"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=1190"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=1190"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}